## Writing Style Guidelines

### Never Use Em Dashes (—)

**Rule:** NEVER use em dashes (—) in any documents. They are strongly associated with AI-generated content.

**Instead, use:**
- Semicolons (;) for contrasting or clarifying clauses
- Commas (,) for additional information
- Periods (.) to separate sentences
- Parentheses () for explanatory notes
- "and" to connect phrases naturally
- Question marks (?) to separate questions

**Bad:** `The system is strictly assist-only—never provides diagnostic directives.`  
**Good:** `The system is strictly assist-only; it never provides diagnostic directives.`

**Bad:** `Research will follow evidence—investigation may discover novel patterns.`  
**Good:** `Research will follow evidence. Investigation may discover novel patterns.`

